He is honest most of the time, enjoys classroom time, but gives too much airtime to students.  Generally positive and comes off well-meaning.  Certainly better than some other profs.  I don't think he likes brown-nosers all that much.  He seems fair, but is disappointed when you look disinterested.

if you show that you're honestly trying to understand the material in the course, he's very helpful. can't go in his office and expect him to spill everything. have your own sol'ns. as for tests, try studying off any old tests, if available. one of the better finance profs.
